Function: kill
Section: programming/specific
C-Name: kill0
Prototype: vr
Help: kill(S): restores a symbol to its ``undefined'' status and kill
 associated help messages.
Doc: restores a symbol to its ``undefined'' status, and deletes any help
 messages associated to $S$ using \kbd{addhelp}. This allow to remove aliases
 and installed functions, and reset variables to its starting value
 (which can be performed in a simpler way by using the \idx{quote} operator 
 \kbd{a = 'a}).
